{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Performance",
  "description": "Analyze IPA runtime performance from work unit logs using area-segmented architecture (SEQUENTIAL execution for reliability). CRITICAL: Subagents load steering files via discloseContext() AND save files directly using fsWrite. Main agent NEVER reads intermediate files - Python handles all data loading. Analyzes 4 areas: Activities, Errors, Performance, Code. Generates comprehensive Excel report with 9 sheets. Scalable to any log size.",
  "version": "6",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "newSession": true,
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "IPA Performance Analysis - Area-Segmented Architecture\n\nThis analyzes IPA runtime performance from work unit logs.\n\nCRITICAL: Analyze ONE work unit log at a time using area-segmented approach.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\nARCHITECTURE: Area-Segmented AI Analysis\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nProblem Solved: Context overload when analyzing large WU logs (10K+ lines)\n\nSolution: Multi-pass AI analysis\n- Python extracts data from raw log\n- Python organizes data by analysis areas (4 focused files)\n- AI analyzes each area separately (SEQUENTIAL for reliability)\n- Subagents save files directly using fsWrite (no main agent collection)\n- Python merges analysis into master file\n- ONE Excel report generated\n\nAreas:\n1. Activities - Activity timeline, execution patterns, slow activities\n2. Errors - Error analysis, root causes, severity, fixes\n3. Performance - Metrics, bottlenecks, efficiency, memory\n4. Code - JavaScript ES5 compliance, SQL queries (Compass SQL)\n\nPython Role: Extract, organize, merge, format\nAI Role: Analyze areas, interpret patterns, recommend fixes\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\nWORKFLOW - FOLLOW EXACTLY\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nSTEP 0: CLEAN TEMP FOLDER (AUTOMATIC - NO USER PROMPT)\n\nExecute PowerShell command to wipe Temp folder:\nRemove-Item Temp/* -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n\nThis ensures clean slate and prevents IDE indexing issues from accumulated files.\n\nMonitor workspace size:\n$tempFiles = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object).Count\n$tempSize = [math]::Round((Get-ChildItem Temp -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object -Property Length -Sum).Sum / 1MB, 2)\n\nShow: \"рџ“Љ Workspace Status: Temp has $tempFiles files ($tempSize MB)\"\n\nIf ($tempFiles -gt 50 -or $tempSize -gt 100) {\n    Show warning: \"вљ пёЏ Temp folder is large despite cleanup.\"\n}\n\nSTEP 1-3: USER SELECTION (Interactive)\n   1. List clients in Projects/ в†’ User selects\n   2. List RICE items в†’ User selects\n   3. List *_log.txt files в†’ User selects ONE\n   4. Confirm selection в†’ User confirms\n\nSTEP 4: LOAD STEERING FILES\n   \n   readMultipleFiles([\n       '.kiro/steering/02_Work_Unit_Analysis.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/04_WU_Report_Generation.md'\n   ])\n\nSTEP 5: EXTRACT DATA (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_wu_log import extract_wu_log; extract_wu_log('<log_path>', 'Temp/<ProcessName>_wu_data.json')\\\"\")\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_wu_data.json\")\n\nSTEP 6: ORGANIZE BY AREAS (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_Performance/organize_by_areas.py Temp/<ProcessName>_wu_data.json Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates 4 area files:\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_area_activities.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_area_errors.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_area_performance.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_area_code.json\n\nSTEP 7: LAUNCH AREA ANALYZERS (SEQUENTIAL EXECUTION)\n   \n   Show: \"в†’ Step 7/12: Launching 4 analyzers sequentially...\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 1/4: Activities\n   \n   Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 1/4: Activity timeline...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"wu-activity-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load steering files\\n\\ndiscloseContext(name='work-unit-analysis')\\ndiscloseContext(name='wu-report-generation')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Analyze activities\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_area_activities.json\\n\\nAnalyze activity execution patterns, identify slow activities (>5s), calculate statistics.\\n\\nSTEP 3: Save analysis\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_activities.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening brace `{` and ending with `}`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing activity timeline\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 1/4 complete: Activities\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 2/4: Errors\n   \n   Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 2/4: Error analysis...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"wu-error-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load steering files\\n\\ndiscloseContext(name='work-unit-analysis')\\ndiscloseContext(name='wu-report-generation')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Analyze errors\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_area_errors.json\\n\\nAnalyze error messages, determine severity, identify root causes, suggest fixes.\\n\\nSTEP 3: Save analysis\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_errors.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening brace `{` and ending with `}`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing errors and root causes\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 2/4 complete: Errors\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 3/4: Performance\n   \n   Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 3/4: Performance metrics...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"wu-performance-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load steering files\\n\\ndiscloseContext(name='work-unit-analysis')\\ndiscloseContext(name='wu-report-generation')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Analyze performance\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_area_performance.json\\n\\nAnalyze performance metrics, identify bottlenecks, calculate efficiency ratings.\\n\\nSTEP 3: Save analysis\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_performance.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening brace `{` and ending with `}`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing performance and bottlenecks\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 3/4 complete: Performance\"\n   \n   ANALYZER 4/4: Code\n   \n   Show: \"в†’ Analyzer 4/4: Code review...\"\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"wu-code-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load steering files\\n\\ndiscloseContext(name='work-unit-analysis')\\ndiscloseContext(name='compass-sql')\\ndiscloseContext(name='ipa-ipd-guide')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Analyze code\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_area_code.json\\n\\nAnalyze JavaScript ES5 compliance and SQL queries (Compass SQL).\\n\\nSTEP 3: Save analysis\\n\\nSave your analysis to 'Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_code.json' using fsWrite().\\n\\nYour output MUST be valid JSON starting with opening brace `{` and ending with `}`.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing JavaScript and SQL code\"\n   )\n   \n   Show: \"вњ“ Analyzer 4/4 complete: Code\"\n   Show: \"вњ“ All 4 analyzers complete\"\n   \n   IMPORTANT: Sequential execution prevents resource exhaustion.\n   Each subagent saves its own output file directly using fsWrite().\n\nSTEP 8: VERIFY SUBAGENT OUTPUTS\n   \n   CRITICAL: DO NOT READ SUBAGENT OUTPUTS - Python merges all data automatically\n   \n   Verify all files were saved by subagents (Test-Path only, DO NOT READ):\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_activities.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_errors.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_performance.json\")\n   executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_analysis_code.json\")\n   \n   If any file is missing, STOP and report error.\n   DO NOT READ the files - they will be merged by Python in Step 9.\n\nSTEP 9: MERGE ANALYSIS (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_Performance/merge_analysis.py Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates: Temp/<ProcessName>_master_analysis.json\n\nSTEP 10: CONFIRM REPORT GENERATION (AI)\n   \n   CRITICAL: DO NOT READ MASTER ANALYSIS - Python tool handles all data loading\n   \n   Show summary of what was processed:\n   - Client: <Client>\n   - RICE Item: <RICE>\n   - Process: <ProcessName>\n   - Work Unit: <WU Number>\n   - Areas analyzed: Activities, Errors, Performance, Code\n   \n   Ask: \"Generate performance report with this analysis?\"\n   WAIT for user confirmation\n   \n   NOTE: The generate_performance_report.py tool will:\n   - Load master analysis automatically\n   - Build wu_data structure\n   - Call wu_master_template.py\n   - Handle all data processing\n\nSTEP 11: GENERATE REPORT (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_Performance/generate_performance_report.py <ProcessName> <Client> <RICE>\")\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Performance_Results/<Client>_<RICE>_Performance_*.xlsx\")\n\nSTEP 12: DONE\n   \n   Show summary:\n   вњ“ Report generated: <filename>\n   вњ“ Areas analyzed: 4\n   вњ“ Performance analysis complete\n\nSTEP 13: ASK ABOUT NEXT LOG\n   \n   Show summary\n   Ask in plain text: \"Would you like to analyze another work unit log in this RICE item?\"\n   \n   CRITICAL: Do NOT use userInput tool - plain text allows hook execution\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\nCRITICAL RULES\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n1. ONE LOG AT A TIME - 1:1 mapping: ONE log в†’ ONE report\n\n2. AREA-SEGMENTED ANALYSIS (SEQUENTIAL)\n   - Launch 4 specialized subagents ONE AT A TIME (Step 7)\n   - Sequential execution prevents resource exhaustion\n   - Each subagent loads steering files via discloseContext()\n   - Each subagent saves files directly using fsWrite (no main agent collection)\n\n3. MAIN AGENT NEVER READS INTERMEDIATE FILES\n   - Step 8: Verify files exist (Test-Path only, DO NOT READ)\n   - Step 10: Show summary only (DO NOT READ master analysis)\n   - Python tools handle ALL data loading and processing\n\n4. PYTHON LIFTS HEAVY LOAD - Python: Extract, organize, merge, format\n\n5. ONE EXCEL REPORT - 9 sheets: Dashboard, Timeline, Metrics, Errors, JS Review, SQL Review, Memory, Recommendations, Technical\n\nPERFORMANCE:\n- Extraction: ~1s\n- Organization: ~2s\n- AI analysis (4 subagents sequential): ~2-3 min\n- Report generation: <10s\n- Total: ~2-3 min per log\n\nSUBAGENTS:\n- wu-activity-analyzer: Activity timeline, slow activities\n- wu-error-analyzer: Error analysis, root causes\n- wu-performance-analyzer: Performance metrics, bottlenecks\n- wu-code-analyzer: JavaScript ES5, SQL queries"
  }
}